article.headline: Tarleton State 68, TCU 59
article.story: FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) -- LaShon Sheffield scored 17 points and Norbey Aragon added 15 as Division II Tarleton State beat cold-shooting TCU 68-59 Saturday night. Sheffield was 4-of-7 on 3-pointers and Aragon was 3-of-6 for Tarleton (3-0), which made 47 percent from beyond the arc (9-of-19). John Davis added 14 points, and Mookie Works added 10 points, 11 rebounds and five blocks. TCU (0-1) struggled from the field all night, hitting 41 percent in the first half. But the Frogs were only 7-of-27 after halftime, hitting 26 percent for the half and 33 percent for the game. Nile Murry led the Frogs with 19 points, but he also had five turnovers. Judson Stubbs was the only other TCU player in double figures with 12. The Frogs got 5 points from the bench. Tarleton outrebounded the Frogs 43-29.
